1) Problem statement¶

This project understands how the student's performance (test scores) is affected by other variables such as Gender, Ethnicity, Parental level of education, Lunch and Test preparation course.¶

2) Data Collection¶

Dataset Source - https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/spscientist/students-performance-in-exams?datasetId=74977¶

The data consists of 8 column and 1000 rows.¶

# Calculate the IQR for math_score
Q1 = np.percentile(df.math_score, 25)
Q3 = np.percentile(df.math_score, 75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

# Set a threshold for identifying outliers (e.g., values outside [Q1 - 1.5 * IQR, Q3 + 1.5 * IQR])
lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

outliers = df[(df.math_score < lower_bound) | (df.math_score > upper_bound)]

outliers[['math_score']]

# Capping Outliers using IQR Method (since data is skewed)

# Cap Extreme values identified from Outliers
def cap_outliers(data, lower_threshold, upper_threshold):
    capped_data = np.clip(data, lower_threshold, upper_threshold)
    return capped_data

# Cap the outliers
capped_data = cap_outliers(df.math_score, lower_bound, upper_bound)
capped_data

df.loc[:,'math_score'] = capped_data
